  "prompt": "Where can I get home made birthday cakes at Gold Coast?",
  "response": "Okay, finding homemade birthday cakes can be a bit tricky, as \"homemade\" can mean different things to different people. Here's a breakdown of places to look on the Gold Coast, keeping in mind you'll want to contact them to confirm their baking style and if they take custom orders:\n\n**1.  Local Bakeries (Not Chain Stores):**\n\n*   **Search Google Maps:** Search for \"bakery near me\" or \"cake shop near me\" on Google Maps and look for independent bakeries rather than large chains. Read their reviews carefully. Look for keywords like \"custom cakes,\" \"birthday cakes,\" and mentions of fresh ingredients or a homemade feel.\n*   **Check out these Gold Coast based bakeries:**\n\n    *   **Flour & Co. (Southport):** Known for their artisan breads and pastries, they often do custom cakes. It's worth checking if they offer birthday cake options and have a homemade style.\n    *   **The Pastry Emporium (Southport):** This looks like it could be a good option for beautiful custom cakes.\n    *   **Panya Bakehouse (Southport):** Offers custom cake options\n    *   **BakedGC (Southport):** Creates beautiful cakes.\n    *   **Madisons Cafe & Patisserie (Various Locations):** They do offer cake services as well.\n\n**2.  Home-Based Cake Decorators/Bakers (Online and Word-of-Mouth):**\n\n*   **Facebook Groups:** Search for Facebook groups specifically for Gold Coast residents. Try searching for phrases like:\n    *   \"Gold Coast Mums\" or \"Gold Coast Parents\"\n    *   \"Gold Coast Buy/Sell/Swap\"\n    *   \"Gold Coast Baking\" or \"Gold Coast Cakes\"\n    *   Post a request stating you're looking for a home baker who makes birthday cakes with a homemade style. Be specific about your preferences (flavors, design, etc.).\n*   **Instagram:** Search Instagram for hashtags like:\n    *   \\#goldcoastcakes\n    *   \\#goldcoastbaker\n    *   \\#goldcoastbirthdaycake\n    *   \\#goldcoastcustomcakes\n    *   \\#goldcoastdesserts\n    *   Browse the photos and find bakers whose style you like.  Direct message them to inquire about custom orders.\n*   **Etsy:** Although less common for local pickup, it's worth searching Etsy for Gold Coast bakers who might offer local delivery or pickup.\n*   **Word-of-Mouth:** Ask friends, family, neighbours, or colleagues if they know of anyone who makes cakes from home.  Personal recommendations are often the best!\n\n**3.  Markets (Check Regularly):**\n\n*   **Gold Coast Organic Farmers Market (Bundall):** Some markets have stalls with baked goods. Check the market websites or social media to see if there are any cake vendors attending.\n*   **Carrara Markets:** Occasionally have stalls with baked goods and treats.\n*   **Check smaller local markets:** Search \"Gold Coast markets\" to find smaller, community-run markets that might have home bakers selling their goods.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Custom Orders:** Most places require advance notice for custom birthday cakes. Inquire about their lead time (how many days/weeks in advance you need to order).\n*   **Dietary Requirements:** If you have any dietary restrictions (gluten-free, dairy-free, vegan, allergies), be sure to inquire if the baker can accommodate them.\n*   **Pricing:** Homemade cakes will likely be more expensive than supermarket cakes due to the quality of ingredients and the time involved in making them.  Ask for a quote upfront.\n*   **Reviews and References:** If possible, ask for photos of previous cakes they've made or read online reviews to get an idea of their quality and reliability.\n*   **Communication:** Clear communication is key. Be very specific about your desired cake design, flavors, size, and any other requirements.\n\n**Key Takeaway:** The best approach is to do some online searching, browse social media, and ask around.  Contact potential bakers directly to discuss your needs and ensure they can create the perfect homemade birthday cake for your celebration. Good luck!\n",
